%We have to choose parameters so that $\mu _0$ is sufficiently large that $ \mu_{b.i}(w) = \mu_0 w^{n-1} - \mu_{f.i}(w) - \mu_{p.i}(w)\geq 0. $ 

\item (Equation~\ref{eq:nb}) The resource spectrum extends from the smallest weight at which an explicitly 
modeled fish may eat. We define the carrying capacity $c_p(w)$ of the 
resource so when our system is at steady state, the 
combination of the resource spectrum and the aggregate abundance of 
the explicitly modeled species is the power law $\kappa w^{-\lambda}.$ 
An expression for how we set $c_p(w)$ within the scale-invariant trait-based 
model is given by Equation~\ref{eq:cp}. 
